This paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category as it studies the dynamics of coalition formation in multiagent systems, which is a classic topic in game theory. Additionally, the paper proposes profit-sharing schemes and analyzes the properties of resulting states, which are common approaches in game theory. 

The paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it deals with the behavior of agents in a multiagent system, which is a common topic in AI research. 

The Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category is also likely as the paper specifically studies the dynamics of coalition formation in multiagent systems. 

The Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS) sub-category may be relevant as the paper analyzes the properties of states resulting from the myopic behavior of agents, which can be seen as a distributed computing problem. 

Finally, the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category may be relevant as the paper studies the behavior of agents in a networked environment where they form coalitions and share profits.
